CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 17, 1959, pg. 32, reads: "After Defeating South - Fifth Avenue High School's cagers, pacesetters in Section 1 of the City League, with three wins and no losses are shown after downing South on the latter's court, 69-50. Front, left to right: Theodore Andrews and Lawrence Eleam.  Rear: Gary Kenley, Waddell Fleming, Richard Dunn, David Campbell and Marvin Reed. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Fifth Avenue High School basketball team with Theodore Andrews or Don Campbell and Lawrence Eleam squatting in front; standing from left: Gary Kenley, Waddell Fleming, Richard Dunn, David Campbell and Marvin Reed, and possibly Paul Patton standing in background on right, in gymnasium
